<section xml:id="future-and-present-values-of-increasing-and-decreasing-annuities">
  <title>Future and Present Values of Annuities with Payments in Arithmetic Progression</title>
  <p>
    In the last activity, we learned to identify and denote values of annuities with payments in arithmetic progression.  In this activity, we will calculate those values. 
  </p>
  <p>
    We are going to take the following formulas as given for now.  In a later activity, we will derive them.
  </p>
  <me>(Ia)_{\angln \iota} = \frac{\ddot{a}_{\angln} - nv^n}{\iota}</me> 
  <me>(Da)_{\angln \iota} = \frac{n - a_{\angln}}{\iota}</me>
  <activity xml:id="table-of-formulas-for-increasing-and-decreasing-annuities">
    <statement>
      <p> 
        Complete the following table of formulas, using appropriate notation.
      </p>
      <table>
        <tabular>
          <row>
            <cell>
            </cell>
            <cell>
              Present Value
            </cell>
            <cell>
              Future Value
            </cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell>
              Increasing Annuity Immediate
            </cell>
            <cell>
              <m>(Ia)_{\angln \iota}= \frac{\ddot{a}_{\angln} - nv^n}{\iota}</m>
            </cell>
            <cell>
            </cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell>
              Increasing Annuity Due
            </cell>
            <cell>
            </cell>
            <cell>
            </cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell>
              Decreasing Annuity Immediate
            </cell>
            <cell>
              <m>(Da)_{\angln \iota} = \frac{n - a_{\angln}}{\iota}</m>
            </cell>
            <cell>
            </cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell>
              Decreasing Annuity Due
            </cell>
            <cell>
            </cell>
            <cell>
            </cell>
          </row>
        </tabular>
      </table>
    </statement>
  </activity>
  <activity xml:id="increasing-perpetuity-immediate-formula">
    <introduction>
      <p> 
        Next, consider an increasing perpetuity. 
      </p>
    </introduction>
    <task>
      <p>  
        For an increasing perpetuity immediate, calculate <me>(Ia)_{\angl{\infty} \iota} = \lim_{n \rightarrow \infty} (Ia)_{\angln \iota}</me>  You may assume <m>nv^n \rightarrow 0</m> (although you can prove this using L'Ho&#x302;pital if you want some extra street cred!).
      </p>
    </task>
    <task>
      <p> 
        Adapt your formula to find <m>(I\ddot{a})_{\angl{\infty} \iota}</m>.
      </p>
    </task>
    <task>
      <p> 
        Why are we not considering <m>(Da)_{\angl{\infty} \iota}</m>?
      </p>
    </task>
  </activity>
  <assemblage>
    <title>&#x1F9EE; Calculator Corner</title>
    <p>
      The financial calculator can be used to find <m>(Ia)_{\angln}</m> and <m>(Ds)_{\angln}</m> only.  
    </p>
  </assemblage>
  <activity xml:id="using-calculator-for-increasing-annuities-immediate-present-value">
    <introduction>
      <p> 
        For <m>(Ia)_{\angln}</m>:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            Put your calculator into <kbd>BGN</kbd> mode.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p> 
            Enter the value of <m>n</m> for <kbd>N</kbd>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p> 
            Enter <m>100\iota</m> for <kbd>I/Y</kbd>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p> 
            Enter 1, followed by <kbd>&#177;</kbd>, for <kbd>PMT</kbd>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p> 
            Enter the value of <m>n</m> for <kbd>FV</kbd>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p> 
            Ask the calculator to <kbd>CPT</kbd> <kbd>PV</kbd>.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </introduction>
    <task>
      <p> 
        This sequence of steps does not calculate the entirety of <m>(Ia)_{\angln}</m>. What DOES this calculate?
      </p>
    </task>
    <task>
      <p> 
        How could you modify your entries to calculate <m>(Ia)_{\angln}</m> completely?
      </p>
    </task>
  </activity>
  <activity xml:id="using-calculator-for-decreasing-annuities-immediate-future-value">
    <introduction>
      <p> 
        For <m>(Ds)_{\angln}</m>:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p> 
            Make sure your calculator is NOT in <kbd>BGN</kbd> mode.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p> 
            Enter the value of <m>n</m> for <kbd>N</kbd>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p> 
            Enter <m>100\iota</m> for <kbd>I/Y</kbd>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p> 
            Enter the value of <m>n</m> , followed by <kbd>&#177;</kbd>, for <kbd>PV</kbd>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p> 
            Enter 1 for <kbd>PMT</kbd>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p> 
            Ask the calculator to <kbd>CPT</kbd> <kbd>FV</kbd>.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </introduction>
    <task>
      <p> 
        This sequence of steps does not calculate the entirety of <m>(Ds)_{\angln}</m>. What DOES this calculate?
      </p>
    </task>
    <task>
      <p> 
        How could you modify your entries to calculate <m>(Ds)_{\angln}</m> completely?
      </p>
    </task>
  </activity>
  <activity xml:id="using-calculator-to-find-values-for-other-increasing-decreasing-annuities">
    <statement>
      <p> 
        How could you use the calculator to find other values of increasing or decreasing annuities?
      </p>
    </statement>
  </activity>
  <activity xml:id="calculating-increasing-decreasing-annuities">
    <introduction>
      <p> 
        Calculate the following, using both the formulas AND the calculator.
      </p>
    </introduction>
    <task>
      <p> 
        <m>(Ia)_{\angl{20} .08}</m>
      </p>
    </task>
    <task>
      <p> 
        <m>(Ds)_{\angl{35} .04}</m>
      </p>
    </task>
    <task>
      <p> 
        <m>3 (Is)_{\angl{15} .05}</m>
      </p>
    </task>
    <task>
      <p> 
        <m>5(Da)_{\angl{9} .02}</m>
      </p>
    </task>
  </activity> 
  <activity xml:id="increasing-decreasing-annuities-series-representations">
    <statement>
      <p> 
        To conclude, write the series representations of <m>(Ia)_{\angln}</m>, <m>(Is)_{\angln}</m>, <m>(Da)_{\angln}</m>, and <m>(Ds)_{\angln}</m>.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </activity>
</section>